Below is the **complete, minimal project** that runs a plain Node.js HTTP server inside a Docker container and executes Playwright tests against it—all in a single image.

---

## Project layout

```
/home/pw-demo/
├─ Dockerfile
├─ package.json
├─ src/
│   ├─ server.js            # Node HTTP server
│   └─ tests/
│       └─ example.spec.js  # Playwright test
```

### 1️⃣ Dockerfile

```dockerfile
# Use official Node image
FROM node:20-bullseye-slim
WORKDIR /app

# Install Playwright dependencies
RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y \
      libxss1 libasound2 libatk1.0-0 libatk-bridge2.0-0 \
      libgtk-3-0 libnspr4 libnss3 libxcomposite1 libxdamage1 \
      libxrandr2 libgbm1 libpango-1.0-0 libpangocairo-1.0-0 \
      libdrm2 libwayland-client0 libwayland-cursor0 libwayland-egl1 \
      libwayland-server0 && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

# Copy package files and install dependencies (including devDeps)
COPY package*.json ./
RUN npm ci

# Copy source code
COPY src ./src

# Install Playwright browsers
RUN npx playwright install --with-deps

# Start server, wait for readiness, run tests
ENTRYPOINT ["sh", "-c",
  "node src/server.js & SERVER_PID=$!; \
   echo 'Waiting for server'; \
   until curl -s http://localhost:3000/health; do sleep 1; done; \
   echo 'Server ready'; \
   npx playwright test --reporter=dot; \
   TEST_EXIT=$?; \
   kill $SERVER_PID; \
   exit $TEST_EXIT"]
```

### 2️⃣ package.json

```json
{
  "name": "pw-demo",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "main": "src/server.js",
  "scripts": {
    "test": "npx playwright test"
  },
  "devDependencies": {
    "@playwright/test": "^1.45.0"
  },
  "dependencies": {}
}
```

### 3️⃣ src/server.js

```js
const http = require('http');

const port = 3000;
const server = http.createServer((req, res) => {
  if (req.url === '/health') {
    res.writeHead(200);
    res.end();
  } else {
    res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'text/plain' });
    res.end('Hello from Node!');
  }
});

server.listen(port, () => {
  console.log(`Server listening on http://localhost:${port}`);
});
```

### 4️⃣ src/tests/example.spec.js

```js
const { test, expect } = require('@playwright/test');

test('homepage loads', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto('http://localhost:3000/');
  await expect(page.locator('body')).toContainText('Hello from Node!');
});
```

---

## How to use

```bash
# Build the image
docker build -t pw-demo /home/pw-demo

# Run the container (tests will execute automatically)
docker run --rm pw-demo
```

The container will:

1. Start the HTTP server in the background.
2. Poll `/health` until it returns `200`.
3. Run the Playwright test suite.
4. Exit with the test result code.

That’s all—no Express, no TypeScript, and a single, self‑contained Docker image. Happy testing!

